node.title: NSW COVID hospitalisations climb towards 3,000 as 32 more deaths recorded
node.description: Another 32 COVID-19 fatalities are recorded in NSW, while the number of people in the state's hospitals with the virus increases to 2,863.
node.content: ["There were 32 COVID-19 deaths reported in the 24 hours to 8pm yesterday in NSW.", "The number of people with the virus in the state's hospitals increased to 2,863, while ICU admissions were up slightly to 217.", "A total of 32,297 new cases were reported from 12,450 positive rapid antigen tests (RATs) and 19,847 PCR swabs.", "The latest figures show 27.8 per cent of people have had three doses of a COVID-19 vaccine, while 16.4 per cent of those aged 5-11 have had one dose.", "On Tuesday,\u00a0NSW Health deputy secretary Susan Pearce said tens of thousands of vaccine booster appointments were going unclaimed.", "More to come."]
